#### LXC ABOUT #####
LXC is a userspace interface for the Linux kernel containment features. Through a powerful API and simple tools, it lets Linux users easily create and manage system or application containers.


#### Instalação dos containers ####
https://github.com/buzz66boy/ns3-lxc/wiki/Install-&-Run-ns3-lxc

- Install:
	sudo apt install libyaml-cpp-dev lxc lxc-dev cmake gcc
- Create VMs: 
	cd ns-allinone-3.26/ns-3.26
	sudo lxc-create -n left -t ubuntu -f src/tap-bridge/examples/lxc-left.conf
	sudo lxc-create -n right -t ubuntu -f src/tap-bridge/example/lxc-right.conf

- Add bridge to transmit packets: 
	sudo brctl addbr br-left
	sudo brctl addbr br-right

- Create tap devices that will be used to get packet from the bridges into its process:
	sudo apt install uml-utilities
	sudo tunctl -t tap-left
	sudo tunctl -t tap-right

- Set IP addresses of the tap devices and turn them on:
	sudo ifconfig tap-left 0.0.0.0 promisc up
	sudo ifconfig tap-right 0.0.0.0 promisc up

- Add the tap devices to bridges and bring up:
	sudo brctl addif br-left tap-left
	sudo ifconfig br-left up 
	sudo brctl addif br-right tap-right
	sudo ifconfig br-right up

- Show if containers was created:
	sudo brctl show
	sudo lxc-ls -f	

- LXC requires the cgroups filesystem to be mount. So:
	sudo mount -t cgroup cgroup /sys/fs/cgroup 
  You also could add a line in /etc/fstab to do this.

- A cgroup related erro is likely to appear, so install this package:
	sudo apt install cgroup-lite

- Start the container:
	sudo lxc-start -n left
	
- Acess the container
	sudo lxc-attach -n left

 #INSIDE OF LEFT CONTAINER#
 - Usuário: ubuntu
   Senha: ubuntu
